WEBVTT

1
00:02:46.708 --> 00:02:47.708
Ah.

2
00:03:13.000 --> 00:03:15.083
Yakuza boss:

3
00:03:24.250 --> 00:03:27.125
♪Put your hand
In the hand of the man♪

4
00:03:27.208 --> 00:03:29.708
♪Who stilled the water♪

5
00:03:30.875 --> 00:03:31.875
♪Put your hand♪

6
00:03:31.958 --> 00:03:33.125
In special news.

7
00:03:33.208 --> 00:03:34.417
Normal is celebrating

8
00:03:34.542 --> 00:03:37.875
152 years since
the railway came to town.

9
00:03:38.375 --> 00:03:40.625
Weather advisory
remains on a high level

10
00:03:40.708 --> 00:03:42.875
with a winter storm...

11
00:03:42.958 --> 00:03:44.708
...looks like it's going to--

12
00:03:44.833 --> 00:03:48.083
By putting your hand
In the hand of the man... ♪

13
00:03:50.958 --> 00:03:52.292
So. how's
the motel treating you?

14
00:03:52.375 --> 00:03:55.667
Exactly how you'd
expect for 55 bucks a night.

15
00:03:55.833 --> 00:03:57.083
What'd you do dinner?

16
00:03:57.667 --> 00:04:00.500
I got delivery
from the Chinese place.

17
00:04:00.875 --> 00:04:01.958
Chang Lu's?

18
00:04:02.167 --> 00:04:03.417
Is there
another one?

19
00:04:04.208 --> 00:04:07.167
No. No. Just Chang Lu's.

20
00:04:10.375 --> 00:04:12.958
Have you been to Ernie's
place to try his meatloaf?

21
00:04:13.042 --> 00:04:14.083
It's amazing.

22
00:04:14.708 --> 00:04:15.958
Duly noted.

23
00:04:22.375 --> 00:04:23.542
This is Penny.

24
00:04:23.667 --> 00:04:25.042
Sorry I missed you.
Please leave a message.

25
00:04:25.167 --> 00:04:26.625
and I'll circle
back when I can.

26
00:04:26.708 --> 00:04:28.792
Hey. it's just me.

27
00:04:28.875 --> 00:04:31.125
Ulysses. you know.
your husband.

28
00:04:31.208 --> 00:04:33.708
if you don't mind me
still calling myself that.

29
00:04:34.208 --> 00:04:36.292
I know we agreed
to take some time apart.

30
00:04:36.375 --> 00:04:38.333
that you need space.
I... I get it.

31
00:04:38.417 --> 00:04:40.375
but I just thought
I'd let you know

32
00:04:40.500 --> 00:04:43.333
I landed another
temporary sheriff job

33
00:04:43.417 --> 00:04:46.208
in a little town called
Normal. Minnesota.

34
00:04:47.042 --> 00:04:50.042
Like a lot of small towns.
it's half abandoned.

35
00:04:50.375 --> 00:04:51.875
The other half is nice. though.

36
00:04:52.333 --> 00:04:53.542
People seem
friendly enough.

37
00:04:54.250 --> 00:04:56.833
They built themselves a real
nice little setup here.

38
00:04:57.208 --> 00:04:58.708
considering how hard times are

39
00:04:58.833 --> 00:05:00.958
for most folks
in the country right now.

40
00:05:01.667 --> 00:05:02.958
I don't know
what their secret is.

41
00:05:03.042 --> 00:05:05.500
but I could do with
a serving of it.

42
00:05:05.958 --> 00:05:07.625
Anyway. it's just
for eight weeks

43
00:05:07.708 --> 00:05:09.833
till they elect
the new permanent lawman.

44
00:05:10.708 --> 00:05:14.792
My goal is to leave this town
just the way I found it.

45
00:05:19.833 --> 00:05:21.542
What's the deal
with that jacket?

46
00:05:21.667 --> 00:05:25.375
It's pretty cool. huh?
I got it to match my chopper.

47
00:05:26.375 --> 00:05:28.958
- I didn't know you had one.
- Oh. no. I don't. not yet.

48
00:05:29.042 --> 00:05:30.958
I'm just saving up.

49
00:05:31.667 --> 00:05:33.375
Figured I'd
start with the jacket.

50
00:05:34.792 --> 00:05:36.708
Well. it's loud.

51
00:05:37.000 --> 00:05:38.792
You mean
it's too flashy?

52
00:05:38.875 --> 00:05:41.333
No. I mean it...
...makes noise.

53
00:05:41.417 --> 00:05:43.792
It's literally loud.

54
00:05:43.875 --> 00:05:45.625
And I don't
think it's regulation.

55
00:05:45.708 --> 00:05:47.083
- Right.
- Sorry.

56
00:05:48.250 --> 00:05:49.875
I'll just...

57
00:05:50.000 --> 00:05:52.125
No. no. Just leave it on.
Leave it on.

58
00:05:52.208 --> 00:05:54.125
It's cool. It's very cool.

59
00:05:55.542 --> 00:05:58.125
Whoa. $16.8 million.

60
00:05:58.208 --> 00:06:00.542
Where the hell did this town
get that kind of money?

61
00:06:00.875 --> 00:06:03.042
Community really
came together on that one.

62
00:06:03.708 --> 00:06:05.042
Yeah. I would say.

63
00:06:06.208 --> 00:06:07.417
Hey.
Mayor Kibner!

64
00:06:07.875 --> 00:06:08.958
There he is.

65
00:06:14.792 --> 00:06:16.625
I can't wait
for the parade next week.

66
00:06:16.708 --> 00:06:18.625
We all dress up.
You're going to love it.

67
00:06:18.708 --> 00:06:20.458
I always wanted to be
the parade mascot.

68
00:06:20.542 --> 00:06:21.958
but I never got picked.

69
00:06:22.042 --> 00:06:23.042
I'm not bitter. though.

70
00:06:24.167 --> 00:06:27.208
The guys take their bikes
pretty seriously here.

71
00:06:27.958 --> 00:06:30.250
My bike's probably going
to be a lot like this one.

72
00:06:30.875 --> 00:06:33.708
Jeez. Randy. I wish my
girlfriend was that dirty.

73
00:06:33.792 --> 00:06:35.417
Have you got
a girlfriend. Sheriff?

74
00:06:35.542 --> 00:06:37.958
No. I've got a wife.
She's had it with me.

75
00:06:38.042 --> 00:06:39.875
Then I'll put an
extra sugar in your coffee.

76
00:06:40.542 --> 00:06:42.292
- Is that too much to ask for?
- Hey. Tom! How are you?

77
00:06:42.375 --> 00:06:43.958
Hey. Mike. This is
America. God damn it.

78
00:06:44.042 --> 00:06:45.792
What's mine is mine.
for fuck's sake.

79
00:06:45.875 --> 00:06:47.292
She can't go and
talk to me like this.

80
00:06:47.958 --> 00:06:49.542
I'm going to go put a pot on.

81
00:06:49.625 --> 00:06:51.958
I feel like Sisyphus pushing
a rock up a God damn hill.

82
00:06:52.042 --> 00:06:53.000
What's the problem?

83
00:06:53.083 --> 00:06:54.708
Tom's being a Goddamn dick.

84
00:06:54.833 --> 00:06:56.542
- That's the fucking problem.
- Fuck you. you trumped-up--

85
00:06:56.625 --> 00:06:59.083
Whoa! Just communicate
the problem to me.

86
00:06:59.208 --> 00:07:01.250
Depends who the fuck
you're meant to be.

87
00:07:01.375 --> 00:07:03.625
Well. if I'm reading this
badge correctly.

88
00:07:03.708 --> 00:07:04.958
I'm the sheriff.

89
00:07:05.083 --> 00:07:06.542
Yeah. I sure as
shit didn't vote for you.

90
00:07:06.625 --> 00:07:07.958
I understand.

91
00:07:08.042 --> 00:07:10.708
You know Sheriff Gunderson
died. right? Last week?

92
00:07:10.792 --> 00:07:12.792
This is Ulysses.
He's filling in. yeah?

93
00:07:12.875 --> 00:07:15.083
Yeah. I... I heard
something about that.

94
00:07:15.208 --> 00:07:16.958
- Well...
- So you're his replacement?

95
00:07:17.042 --> 00:07:18.208
I'm the interim.

96
00:07:18.708 --> 00:07:20.708
It's like a substitute teacher.

97
00:07:20.792 --> 00:07:22.083
For how long?

98
00:07:22.208 --> 00:07:23.792
He's on week one
of eight.

99
00:07:23.875 --> 00:07:24.875
Morning. peoples!

100
00:07:25.000 --> 00:07:26.042
Morning. Blaine.
Ooh. donuts.

101
00:07:26.167 --> 00:07:27.125
- Hey. Old-fashioned?
- Okay. Well. so.

102
00:07:27.208 --> 00:07:28.708
Carl keeps parking
his Goddamn--

103
00:07:28.792 --> 00:07:30.083
- Carl's his neighbor.
- My neighbor keeps

104
00:07:30.208 --> 00:07:31.417
parking his God damn rig
in my driveway.

105
00:07:31.542 --> 00:07:32.708
- It's a tow truck.
- I see.

106
00:07:32.833 --> 00:07:34.083
Carl has his own
tow trucking company.

107
00:07:34.208 --> 00:07:35.875
- has since high school.
- Hey. Mike.

108
00:07:35.958 --> 00:07:37.500
I lived there first.
It's my property just as much--

109
00:07:37.583 --> 00:07:39.333
Tom's on a flag lot. so they
have to share a driveway.

110
00:07:39.417 --> 00:07:41.625
He's blocking me in!
That fucker's taking 70 percent.

111
00:07:41.708 --> 00:07:43.167
Hang on! Hang on!

112
00:07:44.833 --> 00:07:46.708
Look. You want me
to drive out there

113
00:07:46.792 --> 00:07:48.208
and sort this out
with Carl for you?

114
00:07:48.333 --> 00:07:50.625
Finally. Please.

115
00:07:50.708 --> 00:07:53.250
Okay. Then I best
head out there pronto.

116
00:07:54.208 --> 00:07:57.958
Uh. we're good? All righty.
Then I'll retire to my boudoir.

117
00:07:58.042 --> 00:07:59.042
Hey.

118
00:08:01.083 --> 00:08:02.708
How's that badge. Sheriff?

119
00:08:03.958 --> 00:08:05.000
Keeping it
warm for me?

120
00:08:05.625 --> 00:08:08.042
I'm doing my best.

121
00:08:08.208 --> 00:08:10.708
Election's in six weeks.

122
00:08:10.833 --> 00:08:11.875
Remember to vote for me.

123
00:08:11.958 --> 00:08:13.542
Sure.

124
00:08:13.667 --> 00:08:16.708
Good people.
small problems.

125
00:08:16.792 --> 00:08:19.792
and if my instincts tell me
something is seriously amiss.

126
00:08:19.875 --> 00:08:21.500
well. then I'll get involved.

127
00:08:22.667 --> 00:08:25.500
But yeah. I kind of stopped
trusting my instincts.

128
00:08:26.625 --> 00:08:28.958
It's not that I don't care
anymore. Penny.

129
00:08:29.042 --> 00:08:33.042
It's just. life's a lot easier
when you care a little less.

130
00:08:34.000 --> 00:08:35.875
Then again.
we are who we are.

131
00:08:46.875 --> 00:08:49.042
Nothing to see here.

132
00:09:28.042 --> 00:09:30.625
Oh. there you are. Refill?

133
00:09:31.208 --> 00:09:33.875
What? Oh. Yeah. Sure.

134
00:09:34.333 --> 00:09:35.958
This is a hell of an armory.

135
00:09:36.042 --> 00:09:37.042
Yeah.

136
00:09:39.250 --> 00:09:40.500
Is that C4?

137
00:09:41.042 --> 00:09:43.417
Uh. that-- It is. Yeah.

138
00:09:44.500 --> 00:09:45.958
Why do you have that?

139
00:09:46.833 --> 00:09:47.958
I don't know.

140
00:09:48.042 --> 00:09:49.875
After 9/11.
Sheriff Gunderson applied

141
00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:52.458
for every anti-terrorism
grant available.

142
00:09:52.542 --> 00:09:55.125
Yeah? How much did
he spend on training?

143
00:09:57.875 --> 00:09:59.208
I should probably get
back to the phones.

144
00:09:59.875 --> 00:10:02.208
Well. the door was unlocked.

145
00:10:02.333 --> 00:10:03.708
That's kind of a no-no.

146
00:10:04.417 --> 00:10:06.542
Oh. Sorry about that.

147
00:10:12.250 --> 00:10:14.417
Every town
has its own little quirks.

148
00:10:15.208 --> 00:10:16.625
You can't change 'em.

149
00:10:16.708 --> 00:10:18.625
Two hundred K.
and the instructions

150
00:10:18.708 --> 00:10:19.875
are in Japanese.

151
00:10:20.625 --> 00:10:21.792
The interim job

152
00:10:21.875 --> 00:10:23.708
is not to get
in the way of them.

153
00:10:24.625 --> 00:10:27.542
I'm like a midwife
with a gun...

154
00:10:28.042 --> 00:10:31.708
...helping 'em
transition smoothly.

155
00:10:41.375 --> 00:10:44.958
Oh. damn it. Damn it. Hey!

156
00:10:51.833 --> 00:10:53.167
I like the way you law. man.

157
00:11:04.500 --> 00:11:07.167
♪I'll trade you my heart
For your heart. baby♪

158
00:11:07.250 --> 00:11:09.292
♪Give you all
My kisses to boot♪

159
00:11:09.375 --> 00:11:12.042
♪I'll trade you my heart
For your heart baby♪

160
00:11:12.167 --> 00:11:14.542
♪Give you all
My kisses to boot... ♪

161
00:11:14.667 --> 00:11:16.875
Hey. Sheriff.
Welcome to my place.

162
00:11:17.000 --> 00:11:18.167
Oh. you're Ernie?

163
00:11:18.250 --> 00:11:20.458
Yeah. just like my dad
and my granddad before me.

164
00:11:20.542 --> 00:11:23.792
Oh. yeah. Tell me.
What's the story with the decor?

165
00:11:23.875 --> 00:11:25.792
Well. Granddad started
collecting 'em after the war.

166
00:11:25.875 --> 00:11:27.375
and he didn't stop
till the day he died.

167
00:11:28.208 --> 00:11:29.625
Any of them loaded?

168
00:11:30.042 --> 00:11:31.833
Wouldn't be much fun
if they weren't. would it?

169
00:11:34.667 --> 00:11:38.042
So. what can I get you?

170
00:11:38.167 --> 00:11:40.042
Uh. I heard good things
about the meatloaf.

171
00:11:40.167 --> 00:11:41.375
Sure. Coming up.

172
00:11:42.042 --> 00:11:44.000
You got to try the pie
before you leave town.

173
00:11:44.083 --> 00:11:45.042
Hmm.

174
00:11:45.125 --> 00:11:46.458
...dropping temperatures.

175
00:11:46.542 --> 00:11:47.958
Snow is much more likely.

176
00:11:48.042 --> 00:11:49.958
making this our first big
winter storm of the season.

177
00:11:50.042 --> 00:11:51.708
and whoo-whee.
does this look like a doozy.

178
00:11:51.833 --> 00:11:54.792
Fucking weather.
Fucking Minnesota.

179
00:11:54.875 --> 00:11:56.875
...plans
to issue a shelter in place

180
00:11:56.958 --> 00:11:58.875
warning around noon tomorrow.

181
00:12:01.792 --> 00:12:04.042
♪Bang bang♪

182
00:12:04.167 --> 00:12:05.333
♪Bang bang♪

183
00:12:54.708 --> 00:12:57.208
Say cheese.

184
00:12:58.250 --> 00:12:59.667
What's going on.
Officer?

185
00:12:59.958 --> 00:13:03.083
Uh. I think a moose
just stole your paint.

186
00:13:05.000 --> 00:13:07.375
It is going to be
a busy day today.

187
00:13:08.042 --> 00:13:10.167
I wanted to get your stamp
of approval

188
00:13:10.250 --> 00:13:11.625
on the parade route.

189
00:13:11.708 --> 00:13:13.625
- Okay.
- There's an intersection

190
00:13:13.708 --> 00:13:16.542
that I think are just
a real hornets' nest.

191
00:13:17.167 --> 00:13:18.208
and of course. first.

192
00:13:18.333 --> 00:13:21.083
we have the celebration
of life at the sheriff's.

193
00:13:22.083 --> 00:13:25.708
The... former
sheriff's. that is.

194
00:13:28.042 --> 00:13:29.708
But you don't have to worry
about saying anything.

195
00:13:29.833 --> 00:13:31.333
because the mayor's going
to take care of that.

196
00:13:31.417 --> 00:13:33.792
and there will be food.

197
00:13:33.875 --> 00:13:36.292
It is a potluck.
so it should be fun.

198
00:13:36.375 --> 00:13:37.708
All right.

199
00:13:37.833 --> 00:13:39.708
Anyone
available? There's a situation

200
00:13:39.833 --> 00:13:41.792
with Maynard down at
the hardware store. Over.

201
00:13:41.875 --> 00:13:44.125
Most of my time is
spent on shenanigans.

202
00:13:44.208 --> 00:13:45.708
- low-stakes stuff.
- Report's

203
00:13:45.833 --> 00:13:47.250
two assholes screaming
at each other.

204
00:13:47.375 --> 00:13:49.542
I get to
say "Nothing to see here"

205
00:13:49.625 --> 00:13:51.167
over and over all day.

206
00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:54.958
All right! Just separate!
Separate!

207
00:13:55.833 --> 00:13:58.083
Mike. I need you
to escort old Clayton here

208
00:13:58.208 --> 00:13:59.333
from the premises
and arrest him!

209
00:13:59.417 --> 00:14:01.208
- For what?
- For being a sumbitch!

210
00:14:01.333 --> 00:14:03.792
Sumbitch? More like thrifty.

211
00:14:03.875 --> 00:14:06.250
Amazon's got these
damn near 30 percent off!

212
00:14:06.375 --> 00:14:07.958
Okay. To be fair. Maynard
that seems...

213
00:14:08.042 --> 00:14:09.000
This is America. damn it.

214
00:14:09.167 --> 00:14:10.542
- The customer is always right.
- ...like a fair price.

215
00:14:10.667 --> 00:14:11.625
That's not helping.

216
00:14:11.708 --> 00:14:12.708
Oh. the customer
is always right

217
00:14:12.833 --> 00:14:14.208
when he's trying
to bankrupt the shop-keep?

218
00:14:14.333 --> 00:14:15.375
No. no. Calm down. Calm down.

219
00:14:15.500 --> 00:14:16.792
Listen. Sheriff.
I will be damned

220
00:14:16.875 --> 00:14:18.167
if I'm going to let some old--

221
00:14:18.250 --> 00:14:21.292
Like you need the money!
You look like an angry thumb!

222
00:14:21.375 --> 00:14:23.875
Go home and be
Amazon's bitch. motherfucker!

223
00:14:24.000 --> 00:14:25.250
Guys.

224
00:14:25.375 --> 00:14:27.542
Guys! Guys!

225
00:14:28.625 --> 00:14:32.083
Maybe we just want to bring
the temperature down

226
00:14:32.208 --> 00:14:33.167
a little bit

227
00:14:33.250 --> 00:14:37.667
in front of the temporary
guest from out of town.

228
00:14:38.833 --> 00:14:39.875
Am I right?

229
00:14:40.208 --> 00:14:42.125
Maybe we should
go for a walk. hey?

230
00:14:42.208 --> 00:14:43.958
- Okay! I'm going!
- Huh. Clayton? Okay.

231
00:14:44.042 --> 00:14:45.625
- I'm going!
- Let's go.

232
00:14:45.708 --> 00:14:47.042
Clayton. this is America.

233
00:14:47.167 --> 00:14:49.958
which means you can't walk out
of a store without paying.

234
00:14:50.042 --> 00:14:51.375
- That's a good point.
- It's called shoplifting.

235
00:14:51.500 --> 00:14:52.917
Maynard.
you thieving motherfucker!

236
00:14:53.042 --> 00:14:56.250
Enjoy your long walk
in the snow. you geriatric tool!

237
00:14:56.375 --> 00:14:58.542
- Sumbitch!
- Okay. Come on now.

238
00:14:58.625 --> 00:14:59.875
Asshole!

239
00:15:00.417 --> 00:15:02.042
How often does that happen?

240
00:15:03.000 --> 00:15:04.542
Once. twice a week
if I'm lucky.

241
00:15:04.667 --> 00:15:06.333
and it's not like
he needs the money.

242
00:15:06.417 --> 00:15:08.083
He just likes pissing up my leg.

243
00:15:08.208 --> 00:15:10.792
Whoa. There's a lot
of locks on that cabinet.

244
00:15:10.875 --> 00:15:12.000
What's going on there?

245
00:15:12.667 --> 00:15:13.833
Stump removers.

246
00:15:14.500 --> 00:15:15.958
Uh. what does that mean?

247
00:15:16.542 --> 00:15:19.000
Old-school
stump removers.

248
00:15:20.042 --> 00:15:22.875
I still don't know exactly
what you're talking about.

249
00:15:23.000 --> 00:15:24.208
Sheriff. come quick!

250
00:15:24.333 --> 00:15:27.208
What? I want
to hear your answer.

251
00:15:30.542 --> 00:15:32.125
It's the yarn?
What-- What about it?

252
00:15:32.208 --> 00:15:34.417
It's the yarn. I--
I-- Look. Look.

253
00:15:34.542 --> 00:15:36.958
I'm sorry. This is
your "Sheriff. come quick"?

254
00:15:37.042 --> 00:15:40.292
I ordered pink.
and they gave me mauve.

255
00:15:40.375 --> 00:15:41.792
Uh. not to play
devil's advocate.

256
00:15:41.875 --> 00:15:43.417
but that is not pink.
That is mauve.

257
00:15:43.542 --> 00:15:46.333
Mauve. That's what I said.
What should I do?

258
00:15:46.417 --> 00:15:48.292
Well. I... I'm not going
to be able to help you.

259
00:15:48.375 --> 00:15:50.542
because they look
exactly the same to me.

260
00:15:50.667 --> 00:15:52.500
I'm sorry. I'm color-blind.

261
00:15:53.042 --> 00:15:56.250
All right. Well.
unlike you. Sheriff.

262
00:15:56.375 --> 00:15:58.708
my clientele's a bit more
discerning.

263
00:15:58.833 --> 00:16:00.458
They're not color-blind.
No offense.

264
00:16:00.542 --> 00:16:01.792
Mike?

265
00:16:01.875 --> 00:16:03.208
Are you there? Over.

266
00:16:04.875 --> 00:16:06.958
Mike. come on. Pick up.
Are you still with the sheriff?

267
00:16:07.042 --> 00:16:08.542
Is that a police
scanner you got?

268
00:16:08.667 --> 00:16:09.958
You keeping tabs on me?

269
00:16:10.042 --> 00:16:13.417
Yes. sir. and a CB radio.

270
00:16:13.542 --> 00:16:16.250
- Oh.
- I get lonely.

271
00:16:16.375 --> 00:16:17.875
And nosy.

272
00:16:18.208 --> 00:16:19.792
Copy that. Sally.
I'm on my way.

273
00:16:19.875 --> 00:16:20.958
Take care.

274
00:16:23.042 --> 00:16:24.792
Call the fire
department next time.

275
00:16:25.375 --> 00:16:28.042
- Oh. I...
- I'm kidding.

276
00:16:33.375 --> 00:16:35.042
Your buck goes a lot
further out here.

277
00:16:35.167 --> 00:16:36.292
That's for sure.

278
00:16:36.375 --> 00:16:39.792
Gunderson had got himself
the Big Mac of McMansions.

279
00:16:39.875 --> 00:16:41.708
He must have issued a hell of
a lot of parking tickets

280
00:16:41.833 --> 00:16:43.042
to get that.

281
00:16:43.167 --> 00:16:45.458
So. what do you say about
a man like Gunderson?

282
00:16:45.542 --> 00:16:48.375
He was a son of a bitch.

283
00:16:48.500 --> 00:16:50.375
But he was our son of a bitch.

284
00:16:50.500 --> 00:16:52.167
- Boss?
- He was a great golfer. right?

285
00:16:52.250 --> 00:16:54.250
- Boss.
- A medium fisherman and...

286
00:16:54.375 --> 00:16:55.833
Oh. What's up?

287
00:16:56.667 --> 00:16:58.042
You got to get
in on this.

288
00:16:58.542 --> 00:17:00.792
This is just like Christmas.

289
00:17:00.875 --> 00:17:02.792
You got
Pete's meats.

290
00:17:03.625 --> 00:17:05.292
fortune cookies.
all you can eat.

291
00:17:05.375 --> 00:17:07.042
You want me to make you a plate?

292
00:17:08.042 --> 00:17:11.000
Uh. not unless I want
to end up like Gunderson.

293
00:17:11.083 --> 00:17:12.500
Oh. That reminds me.

294
00:17:15.708 --> 00:17:17.250
I think you should
be wearing this.

295
00:17:19.667 --> 00:17:21.417
But I thought you
said you had only one.

296
00:17:21.542 --> 00:17:25.708
I did. but when the visitation
was over and done with.

297
00:17:25.792 --> 00:17:29.042
I nicked it off of the corpse

298
00:17:30.167 --> 00:17:32.792
before they closed the casket.

299
00:17:32.875 --> 00:17:36.542
So. you enjoy
the power while it lasts.

300
00:18:03.083 --> 00:18:04.958
Oh. what a trip that was.

301
00:18:05.042 --> 00:18:07.458
Those Japanese sure
love their golf.

302
00:18:10.000 --> 00:18:12.375
So. what'd you pick?

303
00:18:13.208 --> 00:18:15.417
Oh. Uh. Ashford something.

304
00:18:15.542 --> 00:18:19.875
I always tend to lean
toward the Irish.

305
00:18:20.875 --> 00:18:22.042
Seven Gs a bottle.

306
00:18:25.500 --> 00:18:27.208
Dr. Velie.
- - Ulysses.

307
00:18:28.208 --> 00:18:31.708
Um. you signed. uh.

308
00:18:31.792 --> 00:18:33.833
Sheriff Gunderson's
death certificate. right?

309
00:18:34.500 --> 00:18:36.208
Sadly. yes. I did.

310
00:18:36.833 --> 00:18:38.000
What happened there?

311
00:18:39.167 --> 00:18:42.542
Well. a couple Wednesdays ago.
around three in the morning.

312
00:18:42.625 --> 00:18:44.292
Deputy Blaine found him out back

313
00:18:44.375 --> 00:18:46.875
in little more than
his tighty-whities.

314
00:18:47.000 --> 00:18:51.208
frozen like a chunk of ice
chiseled by a chainsaw.

315
00:18:51.833 --> 00:18:53.708
What do you suppose
he thought he was doing?

316
00:18:55.083 --> 00:18:57.667
Not my job to go supposing...
...to be sure.

317
00:18:58.500 --> 00:18:59.875
Gunderson liked his fishing.

318
00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:02.292
He had a fishing rod
in his one hand

319
00:19:02.375 --> 00:19:05.958
and a auger in the other.
so my guess.

320
00:19:06.333 --> 00:19:08.250
man thought he
was going ice fishing.

321
00:19:08.792 --> 00:19:11.042
At night. in his underwear?

322
00:19:11.167 --> 00:19:14.875
Well. as you can see.
the man was a drinker.

323
00:19:15.417 --> 00:19:17.042
And a son of a bitch.

324
00:19:17.167 --> 00:19:19.625
but then again. he was
our son of a bitch. right?

325
00:19:19.708 --> 00:19:21.542
Hey. Doc. Give me a minute.

326
00:19:21.625 --> 00:19:23.167
I'd like to bend his ear. okay?

327
00:19:23.875 --> 00:19:25.708
Now. Yeah. Thank you.

328
00:19:25.792 --> 00:19:27.667
I want to thank you for coming.

329
00:19:28.042 --> 00:19:29.042
Of course.

330
00:19:29.542 --> 00:19:31.042
So. let me get this straight.

331
00:19:31.542 --> 00:19:32.708
Did I hear...

332
00:19:35.208 --> 00:19:37.208
you saw the moose?

333
00:19:37.333 --> 00:19:39.375
I did. I got a picture of it.

334
00:19:39.500 --> 00:19:40.708
God damn!

335
00:19:40.833 --> 00:19:42.875
I am the only one in this
town who has never seen

336
00:19:43.000 --> 00:19:44.042
that fucking moose.

337
00:19:44.417 --> 00:19:46.375
and I keep an eye out for it.

338
00:19:46.958 --> 00:19:48.792
You know.
in Native American culture.

339
00:19:48.875 --> 00:19:52.875
the moose is a symbol
of endurance and survival. Hmm?

340
00:19:54.208 --> 00:19:55.208
- 
--
- So.

341
00:19:56.375 --> 00:19:58.042
what do you think
of our little town?

342
00:19:59.042 --> 00:20:02.250
- It's. um. charming.
- Yeah. You know. I hear

343
00:20:02.375 --> 00:20:05.208
that you are a very
laid-back kind of guy.

344
00:20:05.708 --> 00:20:07.833
not a crack-the-whip sort.

345
00:20:08.542 --> 00:20:10.000
Well. I mean.
I've been known to--

346
00:20:10.083 --> 00:20:11.792
Did you ever think
about settling down?

347
00:20:13.250 --> 00:20:16.208
You could be a real sheriff
for more than a few weeks.

348
00:20:17.083 --> 00:20:19.208
You could build a whole new
life here in Normal.

349
00:20:19.792 --> 00:20:23.875
because we really
celebrate the community.

350
00:20:23.958 --> 00:20:27.958
Around here.
it's always one for all.

351
00:20:28.042 --> 00:20:29.333
- That sounds--
- Mayor?

352
00:20:29.417 --> 00:20:30.333
Yeah?
It's time.

353
00:20:30.417 --> 00:20:31.708
Yeah.

354
00:20:31.833 --> 00:20:33.333
But I want you to
think about it.

355
00:20:33.417 --> 00:20:34.667
- I will.
- All right.

356
00:20:39.250 --> 00:20:41.208
What do you mean. get out?

357
00:20:41.333 --> 00:20:43.542
Why is that of your--

358
00:20:43.625 --> 00:20:44.500
Fine.

359
00:20:46.167 --> 00:20:47.875
Have you
been sleeping in your van?

360
00:20:48.708 --> 00:20:50.083
What? What?

361
00:20:50.208 --> 00:20:51.500
You're a mess.

362
00:20:52.875 --> 00:20:54.792
You're not
the sheriff yet. Blaine!

363
00:20:56.250 --> 00:20:57.417
Hey. boss.

364
00:20:58.708 --> 00:21:00.417
I was just.
uh. checking on you.

365
00:21:00.542 --> 00:21:03.958
- Uh... you good?
- I'm fine.

366
00:21:04.042 --> 00:21:06.167
Well. I just wanted to let
you know that they put out

367
00:21:06.250 --> 00:21:08.542
more of those mini eggrolls.
They're custom.

368
00:21:09.375 --> 00:21:11.208
And the mayor's just
about to tell the story

369
00:21:11.333 --> 00:21:13.542
about the time he went
on the cruise with Jane Fonda.

370
00:21:13.667 --> 00:21:16.000
SO...

371
00:21:17.542 --> 00:21:19.708
You know
who that is in the van?

372
00:21:19.833 --> 00:21:23.208
Sheriff Gunderson's.
uh. daughter. I think.

373
00:21:24.000 --> 00:21:25.000
Alex.

374
00:21:29.875 --> 00:21:31.625
Here she comes on
Down the street♪

375
00:21:31.708 --> 00:21:33.542
Ain't she sweet with that
Style and that smile♪

376
00:21:33.625 --> 00:21:34.833
♪And don't you know... ♪

377
00:21:36.208 --> 00:21:38.667
Hey. lawman. Up for a game?

378
00:21:39.708 --> 00:21:42.875
Uh. my hands are shaky.
They only trust me with a gun.

379
00:21:42.958 --> 00:21:45.292
Company. then?

380
00:21:45.375 --> 00:21:46.625
♪That's my girl♪

381
00:21:46.708 --> 00:21:47.792
I got to warn you.

382
00:21:48.417 --> 00:21:49.792
I'm not very good.

383
00:21:50.375 --> 00:21:52.542
So. would you say
you knew Gunderson well?

384
00:21:52.625 --> 00:21:55.000
Gunderson? Yeah.
I knew him pretty well.

385
00:21:56.042 --> 00:21:58.167
It was sad. the way he. uh...

386
00:21:59.875 --> 00:22:00.792
you know.

387
00:22:01.250 --> 00:22:03.458
But he liked to drink.
He liked to fish.

388
00:22:03.542 --> 00:22:05.833
So the way I see it. he died
doing what he loved best.

389
00:22:06.500 --> 00:22:07.500
You fish?

390
00:22:07.875 --> 00:22:10.625
Uh. when I was a kid.
with my dad.

391
00:22:11.167 --> 00:22:13.083
- You?
- Me? Fuck no.

392
00:22:13.792 --> 00:22:15.542
Probably the only one
in town who don't.

393
00:22:15.833 --> 00:22:18.958
but in the end. death...
comes for us all.

394
00:22:19.042 --> 00:22:20.042
don't it. lawman?

395
00:22:21.250 --> 00:22:23.542
I'm not getting
a Sheriff out of you. huh?

396
00:22:24.208 --> 00:22:27.083
If you really were. you would.
but are you?

397
00:22:29.875 --> 00:22:31.208
You've been listening

398
00:22:31.333 --> 00:22:33.708
to my internal monologue.
haven't you?

399
00:22:33.833 --> 00:22:34.875
That's my job.

400
00:22:36.875 --> 00:22:39.083
I'm Moira.
the barkeeper here.

401
00:22:42.250 --> 00:22:43.333
Rack 'em up.

402
00:22:44.167 --> 00:22:45.167
Why are you here?

403
00:22:45.250 --> 00:22:47.208
Stop fucking around.
Come on.

404
00:22:48.083 --> 00:22:49.042
I'm all ears.

405
00:22:49.875 --> 00:22:50.875
All right.

406
00:22:53.250 --> 00:22:57.125
I used to be a regular sheriff.
Nice county

407
00:22:57.208 --> 00:22:59.250
with a couple little towns
just like this one.

408
00:22:59.375 --> 00:23:01.500
I married my
high school sweetheart.

409
00:23:02.667 --> 00:23:06.167
- Perfect.
- It was. I was. uh...

410
00:23:07.875 --> 00:23:09.208
pretty proud of myself.

411
00:23:10.500 --> 00:23:13.542
I walked through life
with my head held high.

412
00:23:13.625 --> 00:23:14.875
I knew who I was.

413
00:23:20.167 --> 00:23:21.875
Then this girl. uh...

414
00:23:23.375 --> 00:23:25.542
Her dad. someone I knew.

415
00:23:26.167 --> 00:23:28.833
a. uh. upstanding citizen...

416
00:23:31.708 --> 00:23:32.708
had been. uh...

417
00:23:38.417 --> 00:23:39.875
I didn't believe her.

418
00:23:42.708 --> 00:23:45.958
Short while later. there was
an incident at the house.

419
00:23:47.708 --> 00:23:50.208
Gunshots. and I went in.

420
00:23:51.208 --> 00:23:53.708
And she was
standing over him.

421
00:23:54.875 --> 00:23:57.792
He was wounded.
She had a gun out.

422
00:23:58.875 --> 00:24:03.250
And he was cursing her
for what he'd done to her.

423
00:24:05.375 --> 00:24:06.875
And I told her
to put the gun down.

424
00:24:06.958 --> 00:24:08.292
and she didn't hesitate.

425
00:24:08.375 --> 00:24:10.375
She shot him
right between the eyes.

426
00:24:11.417 --> 00:24:13.042
and then she aimed
that gun at me.

427
00:24:14.208 --> 00:24:16.667
And she cursed me
for not believing her.

428
00:24:20.792 --> 00:24:22.375
And then
we both shot.

429
00:24:24.833 --> 00:24:27.875
Um. I had better aim.

430
00:24:31.792 --> 00:24:32.875
After that...

431
00:24:35.958 --> 00:24:37.708
I got dark inside. and...

432
00:24:41.375 --> 00:24:44.083
I didn't know who I was anymore.
and I still don't.

433
00:24:49.417 --> 00:24:50.500
And the wife?

434
00:24:51.958 --> 00:24:54.333
I. uh-- I was hard to be around.

435
00:24:55.708 --> 00:24:57.000
I still call her.

436
00:25:00.083 --> 00:25:01.542
She doesn't answer. but...

437
00:25:02.875 --> 00:25:04.000
I don't mind.

438
00:25:05.375 --> 00:25:07.708
I live in hope one day she will.

439
00:25:21.333 --> 00:25:22.958
You have one message.

440
00:25:25.875 --> 00:25:27.958
Hey. Sheriff.
It's the mayor.

441
00:25:28.042 --> 00:25:29.125
People are really

442
00:25:29.208 --> 00:25:30.958
liking your light touch.

443
00:25:31.042 --> 00:25:32.542
Have you considered
my offer?

444
00:25:32.625 --> 00:25:33.875
Get back to me
as soon as you can.

445
00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:34.958
Come on!

446
00:25:35.042 --> 00:25:37.792
I want a sticky bun.
God damn it.

447
00:25:37.875 --> 00:25:39.375
I bet I can help
you with that!

448
00:25:39.708 --> 00:25:41.458
Oh. Hi. Officer.

449
00:25:41.542 --> 00:25:43.000
- Hey.
- I mean Sheriff. I--

450
00:25:43.875 --> 00:25:45.375
Got stuck.
- - Yeah. I see.

451
00:25:45.500 --> 00:25:46.625
Yeah.

452
00:25:46.708 --> 00:25:48.292
Which you think
will knock it down.

453
00:25:48.375 --> 00:25:49.708
the caramel or the cookie?

454
00:25:49.792 --> 00:25:51.875
Uh. I guess
the caramel should do it.

455
00:25:52.000 --> 00:25:53.458
Yeah.
That's my guess. too.

456
00:25:56.042 --> 00:25:58.500
- What's your dog's name?
Oh. her name's Olive.

457
00:25:59.542 --> 00:26:00.792
Nice!
- - Yeah!

458
00:26:01.167 --> 00:26:02.792
Hey. Olive.

459
00:26:02.875 --> 00:26:04.083
What a good dog.

460
00:26:04.542 --> 00:26:05.875
My name's Ulysses.

461
00:26:06.708 --> 00:26:07.833
I'm Lori.

462
00:26:09.625 --> 00:26:11.167
You know. I wish these
things had dog food.

463
00:26:13.500 --> 00:26:15.875
- Yeah. Well. someday.
- Yeah.

464
00:26:16.708 --> 00:26:19.500
All right. Well. uh.
watch out for the moose.

465
00:26:20.250 --> 00:26:23.083
Moose?
Yeah. Big.

466
00:26:23.542 --> 00:26:25.375
Be careful. He might
try and paint you.

467
00:26:26.083 --> 00:26:27.083
Moose?

468
00:26:39.833 --> 00:26:41.833
Yeah?

469
00:26:48.500 --> 00:26:49.500
Thanks.

470
00:26:50.542 --> 00:26:52.000
Look. I...

471
00:26:53.792 --> 00:26:55.417
I don't know
if I should say this.

472
00:26:57.708 --> 00:27:00.208
But our mustaches
are so similar.

473
00:27:01.792 --> 00:27:03.375
We're like a couple brothers.

474
00:27:04.417 --> 00:27:05.792
Or at least a couple uncles.

475
00:27:09.792 --> 00:27:12.250
Well. I should probably
get back at it. so...

476
00:27:24.542 --> 00:27:27.125
♪Since you left me. baby

477
00:27:27.208 --> 00:27:28.333
♪I'm out all night... ♪

478
00:27:28.417 --> 00:27:30.458
How can love go away?

479
00:27:30.542 --> 00:27:32.625
I mean. did I take
it for granted?

480
00:27:32.708 --> 00:27:33.875
I guess I did.

481
00:27:34.375 --> 00:27:36.250
I didn't protect that girl.

482
00:27:36.375 --> 00:27:38.167
and I lost you in the bargain.

483
00:27:38.958 --> 00:27:42.333
You said I shut down. Penny.
You were right.

484
00:27:46.542 --> 00:27:48.208
Is this what happened
to Gunderson?

485
00:27:48.833 --> 00:27:51.333
Did he give up
and say. "Fuck it."

486
00:27:51.875 --> 00:27:53.708
walk into the snow buck naked?

487
00:27:54.958 --> 00:27:56.875
Oh. that's a hell
of a way to die.

488
00:27:59.042 --> 00:28:00.958
I'm not doing
anything wrong.

489
00:28:02.042 --> 00:28:03.083
You been drinking?

490
00:28:06.083 --> 00:28:08.875
Not when I was driving.
I pulled off to start.

491
00:28:11.208 --> 00:28:12.875
Bourbon?

492
00:28:17.417 --> 00:28:20.542
- That's very impressive.
- You mind if I join you?

493
00:28:21.792 --> 00:28:23.208
I'd-- Joi...

494
00:28:35.083 --> 00:28:36.500
That's a cool belt.

495
00:28:39.542 --> 00:28:40.542
I'm Alex.

496
00:28:41.208 --> 00:28:42.417
I'm Ulysses.

497
00:28:43.375 --> 00:28:45.417
Can I have the cheap booze?

498
00:28:50.375 --> 00:28:52.250
You're Gunderson's
daughter. right?

499
00:28:55.042 --> 00:28:56.042
No.

500
00:28:57.083 --> 00:28:58.083
Oh.

501
00:28:59.333 --> 00:29:02.792
Yeah. Okay. Um. you're...
you're Gunderson's kid.

502
00:29:03.542 --> 00:29:06.833
He had lots of pictures of you
on the wall in his office.

503
00:29:07.333 --> 00:29:08.375
You got his eyes.

504
00:29:10.042 --> 00:29:13.042
Yeah. Those are old pictures.

505
00:29:15.208 --> 00:29:16.542
He's very proud of me.

506
00:29:17.625 --> 00:29:19.958
Daddy's little girl
going military.

507
00:29:20.500 --> 00:29:22.500
Couldn't keep that up.

508
00:29:25.042 --> 00:29:26.125
You were having an argument

509
00:29:26.208 --> 00:29:28.167
with Deputy Blaine
outside the house.

510
00:29:28.250 --> 00:29:29.375
What was that about?

511
00:29:30.667 --> 00:29:31.792
The mayor.

512
00:29:31.875 --> 00:29:36.167
Uh. he didn't want me
to attend the memorial service.

513
00:29:36.250 --> 00:29:41.875
because he said that I would be
too much of a distraction.

