a drink on you. do you?

1041
01:02:37.792 --> 01:02:41.292
Now. what kind of bartender
would I be... if I didn't?

1042
01:02:43.250 --> 01:02:45.458
Let's trade.

1043
01:02:49.542 --> 01:02:51.417
Uh-uh. fucking slowly.

1044
01:03:10.250 --> 01:03:12.458
Well. drink up...

1045
01:03:14.667 --> 01:03:17.000
so. we can all clean up
this mess you made

1046
01:03:17.083 --> 01:03:20.458
before the Yakuza turn up
and kill every single one of us.

1047
01:03:20.542 --> 01:03:21.875
You. too. huh?

1048
01:03:22.542 --> 01:03:25.083
Just doing what I need to
to survive.

1049
01:03:25.208 --> 01:03:26.542
At what cost?

1050
01:03:27.667 --> 01:03:29.458
My soul.

1051
01:03:31.000 --> 01:03:32.542
Although.
they're cheap nowadays.

1052
01:03:32.667 --> 01:03:34.667
Hell. you sold yours.
didn't you?

1053
01:03:35.542 --> 01:03:37.125
I didn't sell mine.

1054
01:03:39.083 --> 01:03:40.208
I lost it.

1055
01:03:42.542 --> 01:03:43.542
How did you know?

1056
01:03:43.667 --> 01:03:45.833
Bartenders hear
a lot of bullshit.

1057
01:03:47.917 --> 01:03:50.458
You get really good
at sniffing out the lies.

1058
01:03:52.042 --> 01:03:56.208
Your story was true right
until the end. am I right?

1059
01:04:00.417 --> 01:04:02.375
The girl didn't kill her dad.

1060
01:04:04.042 --> 01:04:05.083
You did.

1061
01:04:10.875 --> 01:04:12.042
I shot him...

1062
01:04:14.125 --> 01:04:16.875
right between the eyes
for what he'd done.

1063
01:04:21.125 --> 01:04:22.667
I figured it was justice.

1064
01:04:24.917 --> 01:04:26.417
Now. I don't know.

1065
01:04:27.375 --> 01:04:30.083
I've been avoiding making
any choices since then.

1066
01:04:31.083 --> 01:04:34.292
just watching life
from the sidelines.

1067
01:04:35.000 --> 01:04:36.542
That's my truth.

1068
01:04:37.542 --> 01:04:40.667
Now. you go.
What happened to Gunderson?

1069
01:04:40.833 --> 01:04:42.250
I already told mine.

1070
01:04:42.375 --> 01:04:43.833
Me. fish? Fuck no.

1071
01:04:44.667 --> 01:04:46.417
Probably the only one
in town who don't.

1072
01:04:47.917 --> 01:04:50.458
Gunderson. he had
a fishing pole in one hand.

1073
01:04:50.542 --> 01:04:53.375
like this one.
and an auger in the other.

1074
01:04:54.042 --> 01:04:56.375
So. my guess is he thought
he was going ice fishing.

1075
01:04:57.208 --> 01:04:59.667
Who the fuck goes
ice fishing with a fly rod?

1076
01:04:59.750 --> 01:05:01.208
No one.

1077
01:05:02.917 --> 01:05:05.208
I lied. I killed him.

1078
01:05:05.750 --> 01:05:07.833
Because he wanted
a bigger cut of the deal?

1079
01:05:07.917 --> 01:05:11.292
Because he wanted out
of the job. of...

1080
01:05:11.417 --> 01:05:15.042
...the town. the arrangement.

1081
01:05:15.375 --> 01:05:16.417
Why?

1082
01:05:18.125 --> 01:05:19.292
Missed his kid.

1083
01:05:20.208 --> 01:05:21.917
This town made him choose.

1084
01:05:22.750 --> 01:05:25.667
It's a small town
in every way. you know.

1085
01:05:26.250 --> 01:05:29.083
- small-minded.
- Yeah. I get that.

1086
01:05:30.750 --> 01:05:33.875
- And no one gets out.
- Not even him.

1087
01:05:35.208 --> 01:05:37.042
So. you got him drunk and...

1088
01:05:38.542 --> 01:05:39.917
walked him out and...

1089
01:05:40.042 --> 01:05:41.875
Watched him freeze to death...

1090
01:05:42.917 --> 01:05:46.208
which takes longer
than you'd think.

1091
01:05:46.917 --> 01:05:50.833
Unless you're wet. which he was.
because I poured water on him.

1092
01:05:52.000 --> 01:05:54.208
But I learned something
about myself that night.

1093
01:05:55.375 --> 01:05:57.125
What's that?

1094
01:05:57.208 --> 01:05:59.000
That I can do
what needs to be done.

1095
01:06:00.208 --> 01:06:03.250
- What happened to you?
- Nothing I didn't choose.

1096
01:06:06.042 --> 01:06:08.042
Like I said.
that's a cool belt.

1097
01:06:16.042 --> 01:06:17.667
What the fuck. Sheriff?

1098
01:06:18.875 --> 01:06:20.000
Tell me about it.

1099
01:06:21.875 --> 01:06:24.000
I think he would have
wanted you to have this.

1100
01:06:24.083 --> 01:06:26.083
especially in light
of current events.

1101
01:06:31.208 --> 01:06:33.042
Let's go. Deputy.

1102
01:06:33.917 --> 01:06:36.292
This shit storm
is only gonna get worse.

1103
01:06:49.208 --> 01:06:50.208
Whoa!

1104
01:06:56.417 --> 01:06:57.542
Hey. Blaine.

1105
01:06:58.750 --> 01:07:00.542
Light 'em up!

1106
01:07:03.958 --> 01:07:05.375
Bulletproof. motherfuckers.

1107
01:07:13.542 --> 01:07:14.458
Whoa!

1108
01:07:19.750 --> 01:07:21.708
Hey. Blaine!

1109
01:07:23.542 --> 01:07:25.417
Yeah. Joe? Damn it.

1110
01:07:26.042 --> 01:07:28.208
Did we leave anyone
back at the bank?

1111
01:07:29.542 --> 01:07:30.583
No. Joe.

1112
01:07:31.875 --> 01:07:32.917
And the vault?

1113
01:07:33.875 --> 01:07:34.917
Yeah. Joe?

1114
01:07:36.417 --> 01:07:39.583
Is it... still open?

1115
01:08:07.958 --> 01:08:09.208
Yoo-hoo!

1116
01:08:09.333 --> 01:08:10.833
Answer the phone.

1117
01:08:12.708 --> 01:08:17.417
My deputy is currently securing
the contents of your vault.

1118
01:08:23.333 --> 01:08:24.417
Securing?

1119
01:08:25.083 --> 01:08:28.042
Bricks of C4
have been planted

1120
01:08:28.375 --> 01:08:33.208
in and amongst the Yakuza's
physical deposits. as it were.

1121
01:08:35.167 --> 01:08:40.167
So. to sum up.
if I die. it all goes boom.

1122
01:08:40.708 --> 01:08:42.250
And if it goes boom.

1123
01:08:42.375 --> 01:08:45.833
well. them being
the Yakuza and all.

1124
01:08:46.500 --> 01:08:48.708
I don't think it ends
real well for you.

1125
01:08:49.833 --> 01:08:52.125
If we don't finish this
here and now.

1126
01:08:52.208 --> 01:08:53.417
the Yakuza will hunt down

1127
01:08:53.542 --> 01:08:56.208
and kill each
and every one of us.

1128
01:08:57.000 --> 01:08:58.333
me included.

1129
01:09:00.333 --> 01:09:02.333
But wait. there's more.

1130
01:09:04.375 --> 01:09:05.708
I've got a proposal.

1131
01:09:08.958 --> 01:09:10.292
We tidy up the bank.

1132
01:09:10.375 --> 01:09:14.250
make it look like an accident.
like nothing bad happened.

1133
01:09:15.375 --> 01:09:18.000
Just another Saturday.

1134
01:09:19.000 --> 01:09:20.000
Mm.

1135
01:09:20.708 --> 01:09:24.167
Kenny. you say this
is Belgian chocolate?

1136
01:09:24.250 --> 01:09:25.458
French.

1137
01:09:25.542 --> 01:09:28.333
Mm. Same difference. you know.

1138
01:09:30.500 --> 01:09:32.875
So. that's your plan?

1139
01:09:33.875 --> 01:09:34.833
That's it.

1140
01:09:36.833 --> 01:09:38.500
Just make it seem like
any other day.

1141
01:09:38.625 --> 01:09:39.833
Basically. yeah.

1142
01:09:40.875 --> 01:09:44.958
The Yakuza show up.
their treasure is untouched.

1143
01:09:45.417 --> 01:09:48.500
Nothing more than a car accident
that set off the alarm.

1144
01:09:48.625 --> 01:09:51.375
Life in Normal is normal. calm.

1145
01:09:52.875 --> 01:09:56.250
Calm... cleans messy.

1146
01:09:56.958 --> 01:09:58.042
That's right.

1147
01:09:59.000 --> 01:10:03.625
Why don't I just kill you
right now?

1148
01:10:05.958 --> 01:10:08.083
The only thing your boss
is gonna give a shit about

1149
01:10:08.167 --> 01:10:09.542
is that you messed up.

1150
01:10:11.083 --> 01:10:14.000
I say we play the hand
that's been dealt to all of us.

1151
01:10:15.375 --> 01:10:18.833
You make us look good.
we'll make you look good.

1152
01:10:19.833 --> 01:10:21.250
And maybe you get to keep
the rest

1153
01:10:21.375 --> 01:10:23.042
of your goddamn fingers.

1154
01:10:27.208 --> 01:10:31.167
I'm sorry that I.
uh... killed your mayor.

1155
01:10:31.625 --> 01:10:33.250
I know you liked him a lot.

1156
01:10:34.500 --> 01:10:36.833
Though. he did seem
a bit of an a-hole.

1157
01:10:40.375 --> 01:10:41.375
Okay.

1158
01:10:43.000 --> 01:10:44.542
What do you say?

1159
01:10:45.958 --> 01:10:50.083
Well. it...
isn't much of a plan.

1160
01:10:50.625 --> 01:10:55.000
Well. I'm not much of a sheriff.
but I'm all you've got.

1161
01:11:01.833 --> 01:11:04.250
Hey. Alex.

1162
01:11:04.875 --> 01:11:06.167
Let's a put on a show.

1163
01:11:07.333 --> 01:11:09.208
I'm kind of liking...

1164
01:11:10.667 --> 01:11:11.667
Deputy.

1165
01:11:17.667 --> 01:11:18.667
Fuck yeah.

1166
01:11:20.083 --> 01:11:22.458
Come on. people!
This is the new Normal!

1167
01:11:22.542 --> 01:11:24.333
It's gotta seem
like an accident!

1168
01:11:24.417 --> 01:11:26.958
Like there wasn't
a massacre here. you know?

1169
01:11:27.042 --> 01:11:28.875
Bring it in! Bring it in!

1170
01:11:29.708 --> 01:11:31.417
Look for loose limbs!

1171
01:11:32.375 --> 01:11:34.542
Watch for blood splotches.

1172
01:11:35.375 --> 01:11:36.542
Cover 'em up.

1173
01:11:37.667 --> 01:11:40.833
Winter wonderland!
Let's go for it. folks.

1174
01:11:41.417 --> 01:11:43.542
Make it nice for our guests.

1175
01:11:44.542 --> 01:11:45.667
Let's bring it around.

1176
01:11:46.250 --> 01:11:49.958
Down there.
look for any loose entrails.

1177
01:12:13.833 --> 01:12:14.875
Swear to God.

1178
01:12:15.000 --> 01:12:18.667
I had no idea
about killing Gunderson.

1179
01:12:18.792 --> 01:12:20.167
You believed
that bullshit

1180
01:12:20.250 --> 01:12:21.583
about the fishing rod?

1181
01:12:21.667 --> 01:12:23.458
Sorry.
I'm not much of a fisherman.

1182
01:12:23.542 --> 01:12:25.000
but. yeah. I get your point.

1183
01:12:25.250 --> 01:12:27.542
And you tried to shoot me.

1184
01:12:27.667 --> 01:12:30.250
Yeah. I did shoot you.
but I didn't kill you.

1185
01:12:30.375 --> 01:12:32.208
That's the important thing.

1186
01:12:32.833 --> 01:12:34.958
We're here together.
both of us...

1187
01:12:37.000 --> 01:12:38.083
alive.

1188
01:12:40.333 --> 01:12:41.417
Do you. uh...

1189
01:12:41.958 --> 01:12:43.708
Do you really think
this is gonna work?

1190
01:12:46.042 --> 01:12:47.333
You a betting man?

1191
01:12:48.250 --> 01:12:50.083
To my own detriment.
to be sure.

1192
01:12:52.667 --> 01:12:55.792
I'd put a Benji on the lay.

1193
01:12:57.167 --> 01:12:59.792
Wait a minute. You're--
You're betting against us?

1194
01:13:03.667 --> 01:13:05.875
Oof. We're fucked. huh?

1195
01:13:07.333 --> 01:13:10.000
Well. best get into character.

1196
01:13:28.833 --> 01:13:32.500
As you can s--
Can you-- Can you translate?

1197
01:13:34.333 --> 01:13:37.667
As you can see. the storm here
was something else.

1198
01:13:37.792 --> 01:13:41.083
It knocked out phones.
internet. cell service. hell.

1199
01:13:41.167 --> 01:13:42.917
you name it. it's down.

1200
01:13:43.000 --> 01:13:44.667
Howdy. y'all.

1201
01:13:45.792 --> 01:13:48.708
Oh. he's the interim.
like I told you.

1202
01:13:48.833 --> 01:13:52.083
He don't know shit.
He's. uh. not too bright.

1203
01:13:52.167 --> 01:13:53.750
Deputy Blaine.
you know these folks?

1204
01:13:53.833 --> 01:13:55.250
You want to explain to them
they can't come

1205
01:13:55.333 --> 01:13:57.667
tearing through our county
in a convoy like this

1206
01:13:57.792 --> 01:14:00.250
without getting
a greeting from the law?

1207
01:14:00.333 --> 01:14:03.458
Well. uh. this is actually
Pastor Oyabun. Sheriff.

1208
01:14:03.542 --> 01:14:05.208
- Oh. a pastor.
- Mm-hmm.

1209
01:14:05.333 --> 01:14:06.708
He's got a small parish

1210
01:14:06.833 --> 01:14:08.583
just over yonder
down near Everton.

1211
01:14:08.667 --> 01:14:10.667
What's his denomination?

1212
01:14:11.333 --> 01:14:13.500
Protestant. Ain't that right?

1213
01:14:16.250 --> 01:14:17.292
- Tell him.
- He's mad.

1214
01:14:18.667 --> 01:14:19.750
What's he upset about?

1215
01:14:19.875 --> 01:14:21.292
I think--

1216
01:14:21.375 --> 01:14:24.417
I think that he wants to go
to the bank.

1217
01:14:25.792 --> 01:14:27.833
He can't go
to the bank. We've got the...

1218
01:14:27.958 --> 01:14:29.958
- Yeah. yeah. but...
- There's people down.

1219
01:14:30.042 --> 01:14:31.542
- It's true that...
- Hey!

1220
01:14:31.667 --> 01:14:33.083
Hey. hey.

1221
01:14:33.167 --> 01:14:35.667
- We'll make an exception.
- Make an exception.

1222
01:14:35.792 --> 01:14:38.542
- We'll give you an escort.
- Follow us. Let's go.

1223
01:14:41.958 --> 01:14:44.000
Okay. Deputy Blaine.

1224
01:14:44.083 --> 01:14:46.792
let's take our guests
the long way around.

1225
01:14:47.500 --> 01:14:50.000
Give them a little more time
to fix up the bank.

1226
01:14:57.875 --> 01:14:59.000
Those aren't
the best shoes.

1227
01:14:59.083 --> 01:15:00.042
Yes. sir.
Right this way.

1228
01:15:00.167 --> 01:15:01.250
So. just watch
your step. Come on.

1229
01:15:02.500 --> 01:15:04.042
Well. it doesn't look good.

1230
01:15:04.125 --> 01:15:04.958
I know.

1231
01:15:06.625 --> 01:15:08.000
Careful of the snow.

1232
01:15:15.042 --> 01:15:16.667
The driver was killed on impact.

1233
01:15:16.792 --> 01:15:18.333
as was the bank manager
and security guard.

1234
01:15:21.083 --> 01:15:22.917
Sheriff. you mind
if I show him the vault?

1235
01:15:23.000 --> 01:15:25.875
The church has some papers
in their safe deposit box.

1236
01:15:26.000 --> 01:15:28.625
- Yeah. sure. go ahead.
- Good. Yeah. this way.

1237
01:15:29.625 --> 01:15:31.458
The building's in fine shape.

1238
01:15:31.542 --> 01:15:33.875
Uh. actually. it wasn't
a load-bearing wall.

1239
01:15:34.000 --> 01:15:35.458
Excuse me. Uh...

1240
01:15:35.542 --> 01:15:39.667
As you can see.
the vault. it's untouched.

1241
01:15:39.792 --> 01:15:42.125
Excuse me. Pristine.

1242
01:15:42.208 --> 01:15:44.542
Whoa! The church
has done well. huh?

1243
01:15:49.500 --> 01:15:51.333
Pretty color. huh?

1244
01:15:55.083 --> 01:15:57.292
There's a small garage
On the edge of town♪

1245
01:15:57.375 --> 01:16:00.083
♪ Where the hot rods go
When the sun goes down

1246
01:16:00.167 --> 01:16:02.167
♪ The place belongs
To a Mr. Jones♪

1247
01:16:02.250 --> 01:16:03.833
♪ Who repairs hot rods... ♪

1248
01:16:03.958 --> 01:16:05.833
Why did you invite
them out for food?

1249
01:16:07.958 --> 01:16:10.667
I only know. like. four phrases
in Japanese. and...

1250
01:16:11.833 --> 01:16:13.000
I guess I panicked.

1251
01:16:16.500 --> 01:16:18.542
Is your boss
enjoying the meatloaf?

1252
01:16:21.167 --> 01:16:23.375
This is divine.

1253
01:16:25.625 --> 01:16:27.250
Your English is very good. sir.

1254
01:16:28.167 --> 01:16:29.500
I watch a lot of Friends.

1255
01:16:29.958 --> 01:16:31.708
Who's in for mimosas?

1256
01:16:31.833 --> 01:16:34.708
Should I make a toast?

1257
01:16:36.167 --> 01:16:39.000
- Don't.
- Uh. excuse me. Um...

1258
01:16:41.208 --> 01:16:44.792
I. uh...
I'd like to propose a toast.

1259
01:16:44.875 --> 01:16:47.000
Um... You know. I'm. uh.

1260
01:16:47.083 --> 01:16:50.000
what you might call
a "people person."

1261
01:16:50.083 --> 01:16:53.250
So. this toast is to friendship.
I think it's important

1262
01:16:53.333 --> 01:16:55.083
that I take credit
for this event.

1263
01:16:55.167 --> 01:16:57.542
When I become
the next sheriff of Normal.

1264
01:16:57.667 --> 01:17:01.417
there will be many more
opportunities to come together

1265
01:17:01.500 --> 01:17:05.000
and break bread.
strengthening our link.

1266
01:17:05.083 --> 01:17:10.000
And with Pastor Oyabun
and his friendly. friendly.

1267
01:17:10.083 --> 01:17:14.792
um. congregation.
I think this is a new chapter

1268
01:17:14.875 --> 01:17:18.167
for our town
and our happy arrangement.

1269
01:17:18.250 --> 01:17:22.250
So. I'd like to say
thank you for all your help

1270
01:17:22.333 --> 01:17:26.667
and to many.
many more years

1271
01:17:26.792 --> 01:17:33.375
of friendly people helping
other friendly people.

1272
01:17:49.208 --> 01:17:50.208
Please!

1273
01:17:54.042 --> 01:17:55.208
Oh. shit.

1274
01:17:57.000 --> 01:17:59.792
♪Pop. pop. реер-реер-реер♪

1275
01:17:59.875 --> 01:18:03.833
♪Pop. pop
Peep. pop. pop. oh pop♪

1276
01:18:03.958 --> 01:18:06.167
♪ Pop. pop♪

1277
01:18:38.250 --> 01:18:40.792
Asshole!

1278
01:18:44.083 --> 01:18:45.542
Hey!
Get your hands off!

1279
01:18:47.042 --> 01:18:51.042
♪Everybody wants her
Everybody loves her♪

1280
01:18:51.333 --> 01:18:55.000
♪Everybody wants
To take your baby home♪

1281
01:18:55.083 --> 01:18:58.667
♪When you're in love
With a beautiful woman♪

1282
01:18:59.083 --> 01:19:02.833
- You watch your friends♪
- You watch your friends♪

1283
01:19:03.208 --> 01:19:07.083
♪When you're in love
With a beautiful woman♪

1284
01:19:07.667 --> 01:19:09.250
It never ends♪

1285
01:19:09.333 --> 01:19:11.250
It never ends
You know it never end♪

1286
01:19:12.375 --> 01:19:16.583
♪You know that it's crazy
You wanna trust her♪

1287
01:19:16.667 --> 01:19:20.333
♪Then somebody hangs up
When you answer the phone ♪

1288
01:19:20.417 --> 01:19:24.000
♪When you're in love
With a beautiful woman♪

1289
01:19:24.667 --> 01:19:26.333
♪You go it alone ♪

1290
01:19:30.542 --> 01:19:33.833
♪Maybe it's just
An ego problem♪

1291
01:19:33.958 --> 01:19:36.875
♪Problem is I've been
